Structure .
As in the nominotypical subspecies. Head (
Figs. 43–44
) elongate, porrect, anteocular part 0.4 times as long as length of head, 2.1–2.2 ( 3 ) / 1.95 –2.0 (Ƥ) times as broad across eyes as interocular distance; clypeus more or less strongly elevated; vertex distinctly impressed between and anteriad of eyes; eye of medium size, globose, situated dorsolaterally, far remote from ventral outline of head in lateral aspect ( 3 , Ƥ); antennal segment II about 1.25 times as long as segment I. Thorax (
Figs. 43–44
). Pronotum 1.35–1.4 times as broad across humeri as total length; posterior lobe 1.1–1.2 times as long ( 3 ) or subequal in length (Ƥ) to anterior lobe, about 1.5–1.55 ( 3 ) / 1.4–1.45 (Ƥ) times as broad across humeri as greatest width of anterior lobe; scutellum long, apical prongs straight; fore wing reaching to ( 3 ) or slightly remote from (Ƥ) apex of tergite VII. Legs . Fore femur about 4.0– 4.1 ( 3 ) / 3.55–3.6 (Ƥ) times as long as its greatest diameter; fore tibia straight, apex broadly widened and laterally compressed forming a distinct dorsal carina occupying about two-fifth of the total length of the segment. Pregenital abdomen without pecularities.

